languageModelTools.modelDescription:
Sets the Makerchip IDE layout of an open IDE panel from a state object. You can restore a previously saved state OR craft a custom layout defining pane arrangement, splits, tabs, and active panes.

The state is either a TabbedView (single pane container with tabs) or FlexSplit (split layout with left/right or top/bottom sides). FlexSplit sides recursively contain TabbedView or nested FlexSplit states.

Available pane mnemonics: Use makerchip_get_available_panes to get the complete list. Main panes: Log, Nav-TLV, Diagram, Viz, Waveform should typically be included. Other "static panes" and any third-party panes loaded using makerchip_open_third_party_pane are also available.

EXAMPLES:

Single view with tabs: {"panes": ["Diagram", "Waveform", ...], "activePane": "Diagram"}

Horizontal split (Log left, others right): {"sides": {"left": {"panes": ["Log"], "activePane": "Log"}, "right": {"panes": ["Diagram", "Waveform", ...], "activePane": "Diagram"}}, "splitAt": 0.3}

Nested 3-way (Log left, Diagram top-right, Waveform, etc. bottom-right): {"sides": {"left": {"panes": ["Log"], "activePane": "Log"}, "right": {"sides": {"top": {"panes": ["Diagram"], "activePane": "Diagram"}, "bottom": {"panes": ["Waveform", ...], "activePane": "Waveform"}}, "splitAt": 0.5}}, "splitAt": 0.3}

SEE: `.vscode-makerchip/.vscode/skills/makerchip-api-features.md` for details about working with layouts and panes

Opens third-party pane with PDF or iframe content. PDF: uses built-in viewer, supports any URL. Iframe: embeds web pages, subject to CSP/X-Frame-Options. Provide content via either `contentUrl` (a URL/data URI) OR `filePath` (an absolute path to a local file). Prefer `filePath` for local files: the extension reads the file and builds a data: URI internally, so large file contents never pass through the model context. Mnemonic is tab label plus optional `+`-delimited uniquifier string (or allow auto-uniquification). Returns actual mnemonic used (same or uniquified).

EXAMPLES:

Local file (preferred for local content): {"mnemonic": "Guide", "contentType": "iframe", "contentParams": {"filePath": "/home/user/docs/guide.html"}}

PDF URL: {"mnemonic": "Guide", "contentType": "pdf", "contentParams": {"contentUrl": "https://example.com/guide.pdf"}}

Iframe URL: {"mnemonic": "Docs", "contentType": "iframe", "contentParams": {"contentUrl": "https://docs.example.com"}, "options": {"background": true}}

Sets active cycle, updating all "live" panes (Nav-TLV, Diagram, VIZ, Waveform). Provide either 'cycle' for absolute positioning or 'offset' for relative positioning (mutually exclusive). Final value clamped to [0, endCycle].

EXAMPLES:
- Jump to cycle 42: {"cycle": 42}
- Reset to start: {"cycle": 0}
- Advance 10 cycles: {"offset": 10}
- Go back 5 cycles: {"offset": -5}
